'''High Tongue''' was a variant of [[Olys Corellisi/Legends|Old Corellian]] [[Language/Legends|language]] in the times of the [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Old Republic]], more than four thousand years before the [[Battle of Yavin/Legends|Battle of Yavin]]. It was considered "the language of aristocrats", much more favored than other Old [[Corellian/Legends|Corellian]] dialects such as [[Hoodish]], [[Socorran]] or [[Vulanish]].

High Tongue was used by [[Ensterite]] Corellians, who are characterized because of their fanatical devotion to their affiliations and their condemnation of inter-planetary marriage. However, as time went by, even the Ensterites abandoned High Tongue in favor of [[Galactic Basic Standard/Legends|Galactic Basic Standard]], which replaced Old Corellian some four thousand years before the Battle of Yavin. They, however, kept using High Tongue for Ensterite regular rites such as the [[Purging Days]].

